PermissibleValues.value: Device Known Inherent Risk of Procedure Evaluation Conclusion
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Known Inherent Risk of Procedure Evaluation Conclusion

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Known Inherent Risk of Procedure Evaluation Conclusion
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Device problems known and documented in the labeling (including both short or long term known complications or adverse reactions).

Concepts.definition: Reported adverse event known and documented in the labeling (including both short or long term known complications or adverse reactions).

PermissibleValues.value: Device Maintenance Deficiency Evaluation Conclusion
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Maintenance Deficiency Evaluation Conclusion

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Maintenance Deficiency Evaluation Conclusion

Concepts.definition: Problems traced to improper routine or preventative maintenance.

PermissibleValues.value: Device Design Deficiency Evaluation Conclusion
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Design Deficiency Evaluation Conclusion

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Design Deficiency Evaluation Conclusion
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The device problem was traced back to the design specifications (e.g. in the requirements, testing processes, hazard analysis, implementation strategy).

Concepts.definition: Problems traced to the design specifications (e.g. in the requirements, testing processes, hazard analysis, implementation strategy).

PermissibleValues.value: Device Difficult to Operate Evaluation Conclusion
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Difficult to Operate Evaluation Conclusion

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Difficult to Operate Evaluation Conclusion
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Device problems including set-up, operation, and disassembly of equipment.

Concepts.definition: Problems including set-up, operation, and disassembly of equipment. Not including reprocessing.

PermissibleValues.value: Device Failure Related to Patient Condition Evaluation Conclusion
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Failure Related to Patient Condition Evaluation Conclusion

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Failure Related to Patient Condition Evaluation Conclusion
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device problem that occurred in part or in total related to the patient's physiology.

Concepts.longName: Adverse Event Related to Patient Condition
Concepts.definition: An existing condition or disease is demonstrably responsible for the adverse event and use of the device has neither caused nor otherwise influenced this condition/disease-related adverse event.

PermissibleValues.value: Device Incorrectly Prepared for Use or Modified Evaluation Conclusion
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Incorrectly Prepared for Use or Modified Evaluation Conclusion

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Incorrectly Prepared for Use or Modified Evaluation Conclusion
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device that is incorrectly modified or prepared for use by distributor, service provider, or user facility.

Concepts.longName: Device Incorrectly Prepared for Use or Modified Evaluation Conclusion
Concepts.definition: A device that is incorrectly modified or prepared for use by distributor, service provider, or user facility.

PermissibleValues.value: Device Infrastructure Failure Evaluation Conclusion
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Infrastructure Failure Evaluation Conclusion

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Infrastructure Failure Evaluation Conclusion
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Device problems related to problems with the underlying framework, systems, and processes of an organization (e.g. as building power supply, network, oxygen systems).

Concepts.definition: The undesirable presence of living organisms such as bacteria, fungi, or viruses or their products (enzymes or toxins).

PermissibleValues.value: Device Labeling Deficiency Evaluation Conclusion
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Labeling Deficiency Evaluation Conclusion

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Labeling Deficiency Evaluation Conclusion
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Device problems that occur as the result of problems with the labeling (including package inserts, instruction manuals, instructions for use).

Concepts.definition: Problems that occur as the result of problems with the labeling (including package inserts, instruction manuals, instructions for use).

PermissibleValues.value: Device Failure to Follow Instructions Evaluation Conclusion
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Failure to Follow Instructions Evaluation Conclusion

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Failure to Follow Instructions Evaluation Conclusion
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device problem related to the user not following the manufacturer's instructions.

Concepts.definition: Problems traced to the user not following the manufacturer's instructions.

PermissibleValues.value: Device Manufacturing Deficiency Evaluation Conclusion
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Manufacturing Deficiency Evaluation Conclusion

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Manufacturing Deficiency Evaluation Conclusion
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The device problem was traced back to the manufacture of the device as opposed to systems used to control the manufacture of the device (quality system). Examples include problems with construction or assembly.

Concepts.definition: Problems traced to manufacturing process.

PermissibleValues.value: Device Repaired and Returned Evaluation Conclusion
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Repaired and Returned Evaluation Conclusion

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Repaired and Returned Evaluation Conclusion
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The device was repaired and returned to the user (reporter) following a reported device problem.

Concepts.longName: Device Repaired and Returned Evaluation Conclusion
Concepts.definition: The device was repaired and returned to the user (reporter) following a reported device problem.

PermissibleValues.value: Device Quality System Deficiency Evaluation Conclusion
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Quality System Deficiency Evaluation Conclusion

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Quality System Deficiency Evaluation Conclusion
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A defect in the processes or systems used in the design and manufacture of the device. Examples include problems within the change control, production, or quality control processes.

Concepts.definition: A defect in the processes or systems used in the manufacture of the device. Examples include problems within the change control, production, or quality control processes.

PermissibleValues.value: Device Training Deficiency Evaluation Conclusion
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Training Deficiency Evaluation Conclusion

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Training Deficiency Evaluation Conclusion
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device problem related to inadequate training.

Concepts.definition: Problems caused by inadequate training.

PermissibleValues.value: Device Operational Context Caused or Contributed to Event Evaluation Conclusion
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Device Operational Context Caused or Contributed to Event Evaluation Conclusion

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Device Operational Context Caused or Contributed to Event Evaluation Conclusion
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A device problem related to the operator's technique or use environment.

Concepts.longName: Device Operational Context Caused or Contributed to Event Evaluation Conclusion
Concepts.definition: A device problem related to the operator's technique or use environment.

PermissibleValues.value: Off-Label Unapproved or Contraindicated Device Use Evaluation Conclusion
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Off-Label Unapproved or Contraindicated Device Use Evaluation Conclusion

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Off-Label Unapproved or Contraindicated Device Use Evaluation Conclusion
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Device problems related to its use during an unapproved procedure, in an unapproved patient, or for which it is contraindicated, or not listed on the label.

Concepts.longName: Cause Traced to Intentional Off-Label, Unapproved, or Contraindicated Use
Concepts.definition: Problems traced to the intentional use of the device in an unapproved procedure, for an unapproved patient, or for which it is contraindicated, or not listed on the label.

PermissibleValues.value: Reuse of Single Use Device Problem Evaluation Conclusion
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Reuse of Single Use Device Problem Evaluation Conclusion

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Reuse of Single Use Device Problem Evaluation Conclusion
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Device problems related to the use of a device more than once when it is designed for only one use.

Concepts.definition: Problems traced to the use of the device more than once when it is designed for only one use.

PermissibleValues.value: Unable to Confirm Device Complaint Evaluation Conclusion
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Unable to Confirm Device Complaint Evaluation Conclusion

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Unable to Confirm Device Complaint Evaluation Conclusion
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The device complaint or problem cannot be confirmed. If possible, choose a more specific reason from among the terms listed in this branch of the hierarchy.

Concepts.definition: The device complaint or problem cannot be confirmed.

PermissibleValues.value: Use Error Caused or Contributed to Device Event Evaluation Conclusion
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Use Error Caused or Contributed to Device Event Evaluation Conclusion

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Use Error Caused or Contributed to Device Event Evaluation Conclusion
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The interaction between the device and the user caused or contributed to the error. This includes inappropriate use of the device or failure to appropriately maintain the device.

Concepts.longName: Unintended Use Error Caused or Contributed to Event
Concepts.definition: The interaction between the user and device, or sample, caused or contributed to the error. This includes unintended inappropriate use of the device and incorrect sample preparation.
